	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Using &quot;SRAM&quot; for Save RAM is just completely wrong. SRAM is a well known and widely used acronym for Static RAM.<br /><br />Using SRAM is ambigious because there is many SRAM chips in the NES system and in the cartridges, PRG-RAM is more explicit you're talking about the one on the PRG bus of the cartridge, as opposed to CHR-RAM.<br /><br />And as you say there is many confusing terms, it's not your fault for being confused.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
