	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: If MMC5 can't save the game, what mapper alike it can?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Alright. Which MMC5 cartridges have all 64KB of WRAM or at least 32KB AND a battery?<br />Do these 64KBs of RAM at 6000h-7FFFh interfere with the 8000h-9FFFh, A000h-BFFF and C000h-DFFF?<br />My configuration is this:<br />0x6000-0x7FFF = Minecraft World save data, must have as much Save RAM as possible!!!<br />0x8000-0x9FFF = RAM for saving processed sprites (e.g. player with or without an armor)<br />0xA000-0xBFFF = I don't know, if I'll need, I'll use this for something<br />0xC000-0xDFFF = PRG-ROM bank that keeps changing on demand; contains most of the game ROM.<br />0xE000-0xFFFF = Always the same PRG-ROM bank with context switching algorithms for interrupts, bankswitching functions, basic functions, math constants, etc.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Bregalad</b> [ Tue Mar 17, 2015 6:35 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: If MMC5 can't save the game, what mapper alike it can?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Alright. Which MMC5 cartridges have all 64KB of WRAM or at least 32KB AND a battery?</div><br />None use all 64 kB of WRAM. <em>Romance of the Three Kingdoms II</em>, it's japanese counterpart and two other japan-only Koei strategy games uses 32 kB, with a battery that backs up <em>everything</em> (see <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/search.php?ines_op=%3D%60%40%60&amp;ines=5&amp;wram_op=&gt;%60%40%60&amp;wram=16&amp;field=2&amp;order=asc&amp;rfa=1+2+11+3+9+20+41+53" class="postlink">bootgod's database</a>).<br /><br />I do not remember by heart, but the MMC5 is extremely flexible when it comes to ROM/RAM bankswitching, so you could have multiple banks of RAM swapped in after $8000 (which is a unique feature). Check MMC5's documentation for details.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Which mappers have a save RAM, PRG-RAM, CHR-RAM, 4 PRG bank address spaces (0x8000-0x9FFF,...), 8 CHR bank address spaces (1KB size each)</div><br />VRC7 seems to be the only one. Though I don't see why you'd want to bankswitch CHR-RAM, Lagrange Point actually does this.<br /><br />If I were you I'd first make something that show a title screen in NROM or something in the like instead of wanting to use the more powerful mapper ever before writing the first line of code (we all made that mistake back then  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" />  )

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


