		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Even if you don't. It lets you take pages away from sprites or background and use them to for frames of animation somewhere else. Say ... 2 KiB of fixed background data, 2 KiB of fixed sprites, and the remaining 4 KiB (and two background slots) can be used for two different speeds of bankswitching four frames of animation of background tiles.<br /><br />It would be a different story if we didn't have 8×1KiB banking.

		

